{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2023-11-08","name":"Guillaume de Chalon Count of Chalon","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Guillaume de Chalon Count of Chalon","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Guillaume"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"de Chalon"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Suffix","value":"Count of Chalon"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"alternateName":"Guy de Châlon (de Thiers)","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1092–1160","fullLifespan":"Abt 1092–Abt 1160","portrait":{"url":"https://tree-portraits-pgp.familysearchcdn.org/bibog/thumb200s.jpg","@type":"ImageObject"},"memoryArtifacts":[{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-904-100649-4433-56/dist.png?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/110657493","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-904-100649-4433-56/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-904-100649-4433-56/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","headline":"de Thiers","@type":"ImageObject"}],"birthDate":"+1092","christeningPlace":{"address":"Châlons-sur-Saône, Saone-et-Loire, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France","geo":{"latitude":46.7842,"longitude":4.8529,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1160","userCertifiedLifeSummary":"Guillaume II de Thiers or Guillaume II de Chalon ( fr.  Guillaume de Thiers or fr.  Guillaume de Chalon , c. 1120 - 3 January 1202 , Cluny ) - Comte de Chalon since 1168 from the house of de Thiers, son of Guillaume I de Thiers, Comte de Chalon.\n\n«b»Biography «/b»\nTogether with his father, Count Guillaume I, he took part in the war against King Louis VII of France . As a result of the war, the king confiscated the County of Chalon, and Guillaume I died in exile in 1168 .\n\nAfter the death of his father, Guillaume II decided to ask the king for forgiveness. He went to Weseley, where the king granted him back the County of Chalon . But part of the county, the rights to which were once sold by the heirs of Savaric de Vergy, remained in the hands of the Duke of Burgundy . He later married the daughter of the Emperor Frederick Barbarossa . In 1180, he fought the Abbey of Cluny , supporting his son-in-law. At the call of the Abbot of Cluny, King Philip II Augustus intervened in this struggle , who forced Guillaume to conclude an agreement with the abbey at the castle of Lourdon .\n\nIn 1186, Guillaume married his heiress Beatrice to Count Auson Etienne III . And in 1190, together with the Duke of Burgundy, Hugo III went to the Third Crusade . He left his daughter as Regent of the County of Chalon. After returning from Palestine in 1192, he abdicated in favor of his daughter Beatrice and ended his life as a monk in Cluny. He died in 1202 .\n\n«b»Marriage and children «/b»\nWife: from 1173 Beatrice von Hohenstaufen ( 1156 - 1181 ), daughter of Emperor Frederick Barbarossa\n\n1.) Beatrice ( 1174 - 7 April 1227 ), Countess de Chalon from 1192 ; husband: from 1186 Etienne III of Burgundy ( 1165  - 16 March 1241 ), Comte d'Auxon from 1173.","sourceList":[{"title":"Foundation for Medieval Genealogy -   [GUILLAUME [II] de Chalon (-[1174]).","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/burgdbchalo.htm#BeatrixCtssChalondied1227A","sourceUri":"Q4G3-FHJ"},{"title":"Leo's Genealogics Website (Leo van de Pas), www.genealogics.org","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceUri":"SRTZ-43N"},{"title":"Ancestry Family Trees","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceUri":"96X1-KQ1"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1092","date":"Abt 1092"},{"name":"Christening","sources":"0","place":"Châlons-sur-Saône, Saone-et-Loire, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1113","date":"1113","place":"Latin Kingdom of Jerusalem","age":"21","id":"G8R1-F33"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sourc